-- Osborne Welcomes Investment in East London Technology Hub
-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 2012-08-02T23:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-02/osborne-welcomes-investment-in-east-london-technology-hub.html
Chancellor of the Exchequer  George Osborne  welcomed investment by  Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) , Central
Working, Gree Inc. and  Barclays Plc (BARC)  in an East London technology
hub.  “We are pulling out all the stops,” Osborne will tell a
high-tech conference in London today, according to remarks
released by his office. “You will not find a government
anywhere that is more supportive.”  Vodafone will create a technology laboratory, Central
Working and Barclays will create a company that supports
business startups while Japan’s Gree will locate to the London
hub called Tech City, the Treasury said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
 gvina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  